 BARBERTON – A smiling Pieter Heijnen collected this life-size Spiderman doll for his daughters, Julia and Lisa, from the Barberton SPCA charity shop last week. According to Marlies Liebenberg, Barberton SPCA secretary, this Spiderman was raffled off by the Barberton SPCA to raise funds for the kennels. Read More: Man fined R500 after sex with chicken Spiderman became a familiar face in Barberton after being on display at book sales in town over the past few weeks. The doll also gained popularity during its visit to Barberton Nursery School, where the winning ticket was sold. “The Barberton SPCA wants to thank everyone who participated by buying tickets and wishes Spiderman the best in his new home,” added Liebenberg.